FBIS3-12060 "drlat061_m_94003" FBIS-LAT-94-061 Document Type:Daily Report 30 Mar 1994 Brazil Fleury To Support PMDB Candidate, Not Cardoso PY3003131494 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in Portuguese 1000 GMT 30 Mar 94 PY3003131494 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [Text] After talking with Finance Minister Fernando Henrique Cardoso, Sao Paulo Governor Luiz Antonio Fleury Filho said he will not support Cardoso's presidential candidacy. He will instead support the Brazilian Democratic Movement Party [PMDB] candidate. He favors holding primaries at the PMDB to choose a consensus candidate for the party. He added, however, that he will campaign for Orestes Quercia. There are three candidates for the PMDB primaries: Orestes Quercia, Governor Roberto Requiao, and former President Jose Sarney, who is a senator.
